WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.900 --> 00:00:02.190
Lesson one.

3
00:00:02.690 --> 00:00:07.280
A geezer and a baby are stranded
on an island full of man-eating beasts.

4
00:00:07.280 --> 00:00:13.240
You rush in to rescue them alone,
but your boat can only seat two.

5
00:00:13.580 --> 00:00:15.160
What do you do?

6
00:00:15.160 --> 00:00:18.920
<b>Former
Marine Headquarters</b>

7
00:00:15.540 --> 00:00:16.790
Umm...

8
00:00:17.410 --> 00:00:18.920
I've got it!

9
00:00:18.920 --> 00:00:23.250
Okay! I'll let the two of them
take the boat while I stay behind!

10
00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:24.750
That way they'll both–

11
00:00:24.750 --> 00:00:26.090
You dunce!

12
00:00:26.880 --> 00:00:28.550
Ouch!

13
00:00:28.550 --> 00:00:29.970
Wrong answer!

14
00:00:30.590 --> 00:00:33.640
That old timer's best years
are already behind him.

15
00:00:34.350 --> 00:00:35.520
So just leave him!

16
00:00:35.520 --> 00:00:36.980
– What?!
– What?!

17
00:00:37.480 --> 00:00:39.440
Just a minute, Vice Admiral Garp!

18
00:00:39.440 --> 00:00:44.730
What did you guys join the Marines to save?

19
00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:47.030
What...

20
00:00:48.530 --> 00:00:51.030
did you guys join the Marines...

21
00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:53.910
to save?

22
00:00:55.430 --> 00:00:57.410
US, US

23
00:00:58.030 --> 00:01:03.270
US, ALL OF US

24
00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:09.700
The end of the dream, the end of the sea

25
00:01:09.700 --> 00:01:12.460
We all have different places we want to go

26
00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:15.240
But to start we've got to show what we're made of

27
00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:19.590
We'll be legends, we're gonna take the world by storm

28
00:01:20.860 --> 00:01:23.180
Sparks are flying, NO LIMITS! This is where it starts

29
00:01:23.180 --> 00:01:24.460
ONE PIECE!!

30
00:01:24.820 --> 00:01:27.440
ALL OF US, I've got a question for you

31
00:01:27.440 --> 00:01:31.030
Have you let the world and all its burdens bring your dreams down?

32
00:01:32.670 --> 00:01:39.230
Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much Every cell in me is getting restless - They're about to blow, oh, it's just too much

33
00:01:39.340 --> 00:01:45.960
Still we try, ALL OF US have our own paths we cling to

34
00:01:45.960 --> 00:01:48.550
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you

35
00:01:47.550 --> 00:01:49.080
ALL OF US, I've got something to tell you If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

36
00:01:48.610 --> 00:01:52.130
If you've got a dream that's worth a damn you've gotta stand tall

37
00:01:53.820 --> 00:01:56.510
Random clues suddenly fit together

38
00:01:56.510 --> 00:02:00.440
Starting to make sense, oh, what's going on?

39
00:02:00.440 --> 00:02:06.910
Threads of time weaving into an intricate tapestry

40
00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:12.610
We can't stop the world from turning, it's changing along with every one of-

41
00:02:13.210 --> 00:02:15.180
US, US

42
00:02:15.800 --> 00:02:20.290
US, ALL OF US

43
00:02:24.040 --> 00:02:31.130
<b>The Final Lesson</b>

44
00:02:34.930 --> 00:02:37.180
What could've done this to a battleship?

45
00:02:37.220 --> 00:02:41.890
<b>Ship Graveyard
Near Marine Base G-1</b>

46
00:02:37.550 --> 00:02:40.220
Was it in some kind of crazy battle?

47
00:02:40.220 --> 00:02:41.310
No...

48
00:02:41.890 --> 00:02:44.350
Those are the battleship bags.

49
00:02:44.350 --> 00:02:46.100
Commodore Brannew!

50
00:02:46.480 --> 00:02:48.060
Battleship bags?!

51
00:02:48.060 --> 00:02:54.530
That damage is evidence of someone using
those armored battleships like punching bags.

52
00:02:54.530 --> 00:02:56.030
– What?!
– What?!

53
00:02:56.030 --> 00:02:57.620
But who could've done that?!

54
00:02:58.030 --> 00:03:01.240
A young Vice Admiral Garp.

55
00:03:01.240 --> 00:03:04.710
It's part of his routine. Has been for decades.

56
00:03:04.710 --> 00:03:05.750
He's still doing it?!

57
00:03:05.750 --> 00:03:07.210
But why are there two?!

58
00:03:07.210 --> 00:03:11.460
The other one belongs to
his old protégé. Former Admiral...

59
00:03:11.460 --> 00:03:12.880
Aokiji.

60
00:03:13.970 --> 00:03:18.300
When training with the battleship bags,
haki and devil fruit powers are forbidden.

61
00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:20.810
You see, the strength of those heroes...

62
00:03:22.010 --> 00:03:24.390
was earned, not inherited.

63
00:03:48.290 --> 00:03:51.290
He sent Sanjuan Wolf flying!

64
00:03:51.290 --> 00:03:53.250
Garp is freakin' scary, man!

65
00:03:58.720 --> 00:04:02.560
<b>Beehive, Pirate Island
New World</b>

66
00:03:59.050 --> 00:04:02.100
Quick, pull him up! Before he drowns!

67
00:04:02.100 --> 00:04:04.680
Huh?! How are we supposed to do that?!

68
00:04:06.810 --> 00:04:08.690
He took that monster out in one shot?!

69
00:04:08.690 --> 00:04:10.520
This guy's unbelievable...

70
00:04:11.020 --> 00:04:12.770
That's Vice Admiral Garp for you!

71
00:04:12.770 --> 00:04:15.150
Just what you'd expect
from the Legendary Hero!

72
00:04:15.150 --> 00:04:17.900
I'm just getting started, boys!

73
00:04:21.620 --> 00:04:25.290
Cut the Legendary Hero shit...

74
00:04:25.660 --> 00:04:29.290
You think you can just wreck
our hideout and get away with it?

75
00:04:29.290 --> 00:04:33.000
How are you gonna make it up to us?

76
00:04:39.760 --> 00:04:42.220
Drunken Spitfire!

77
00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:53.560
Pirate Fireballs!

78
00:05:05.330 --> 00:05:07.330
Meowch, that's hot!

79
00:05:07.330 --> 00:05:09.160
Knock it off!

80
00:05:17.460 --> 00:05:22.180
Are you trying to destroy Pirate Island?!

81
00:05:22.550 --> 00:05:28.310
If Commodore Teach sees
the town like this, he'll kill us for sure!

82
00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:35.020
Why isn't he fazed by our numbers?!

83
00:05:35.020 --> 00:05:37.320
This geezer's off his rocker!

84
00:05:40.950 --> 00:05:43.450
I have a report, Vice Admiral Garp!

85
00:05:43.450 --> 00:05:47.160
Everyone who was captured,
the soldiers, and the injured...

86
00:05:47.160 --> 00:05:48.830
have all been extracted.

87
00:05:48.830 --> 00:05:50.620
Understood. Nice work.

88
00:05:50.620 --> 00:05:52.500
Hibari, stay with us!

89
00:05:53.830 --> 00:05:56.790
Let the frozen ones thaw slowly!

90
00:05:57.170 --> 00:05:59.340
I hope Captain Koby is okay...

91
00:05:59.710 --> 00:06:01.670
We're ready to set out anytime!

92
00:06:02.130 --> 00:06:04.430
Alright! We're through here!

93
00:06:04.430 --> 00:06:07.890
Let's pull back! Koby! Grus! Helmeppo!

94
00:06:09.520 --> 00:06:10.100
Yes, sir!

95
00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:12.060
Got it!

96
00:06:15.150 --> 00:06:17.520
Let's get out of here already!

97
00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:21.240
This really is a beehive!

98
00:06:21.610 --> 00:06:24.950
Pirates keep swarming out!

99
00:06:24.950 --> 00:06:26.450
There's no end to them!

100
00:06:35.170 --> 00:06:36.290
I told you already.

101
00:06:36.290 --> 00:06:39.130
I can't let you guys leave.

102
00:06:39.130 --> 00:06:40.960
Garp.

103
00:06:41.760 --> 00:06:44.050
I knew I should've left sooner!

104
00:06:44.050 --> 00:06:46.010
I'm gonna die! I can't take it!

105
00:06:46.430 --> 00:06:49.310
Garp, I'm the future
of the Marines too, right?!

106
00:06:49.310 --> 00:06:52.100
You still wanna go, Kuzan?

107
00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:56.310
Keep an eye out for Blackbeard's top officers!

108
00:06:58.060 --> 00:06:59.570
Listen up, guys!

109
00:06:59.570 --> 00:07:02.530
All that's left is to run to the shore!

110
00:07:03.490 --> 00:07:05.240
So don't you dare die.

111
00:07:05.780 --> 00:07:06.740
Yes, sir!

112
00:07:12.540 --> 00:07:14.500
Somebody, help!

113
00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:15.620
Oh no!

114
00:07:15.620 --> 00:07:18.000
There was still another captive!

115
00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:19.460
I'm on my way!

116
00:07:19.460 --> 00:07:22.050
Thank goodness we were still here!

117
00:07:22.050 --> 00:07:24.090
You idiot! Get back here, Koby!

118
00:07:24.090 --> 00:07:25.420
It's a trap!

119
00:07:26.680 --> 00:07:27.470
What?

120
00:07:41.520 --> 00:07:42.530
What?

121
00:07:43.030 --> 00:07:45.360
Vice Admiral Garp...

122
00:07:57.210 --> 00:07:59.580
You rat bastard!

123
00:08:03.340 --> 00:08:05.670
A-An invisible man?!

124
00:08:06.050 --> 00:08:07.630
Shiryu...

125
00:08:07.630 --> 00:08:10.800
Impel Down's resident thug!

126
00:08:18.560 --> 00:08:21.190
Wow! Shiryu actually pulled it off!

127
00:08:21.190 --> 00:08:24.400
He managed to stab Iron Garp!
He's vulnerable now!

128
00:08:27.490 --> 00:08:28.820
Garp!

129
00:08:28.820 --> 00:08:29.990
It's nothing!

130
00:08:29.990 --> 00:08:31.910
Just run to the ship!

131
00:08:35.370 --> 00:08:36.870
It's all my fault!

132
00:08:36.870 --> 00:08:38.910
If Vice Admiral Garp hadn't defended me–

133
00:08:38.910 --> 00:08:41.170
Don't flatter yourself, Koby!

134
00:08:41.170 --> 00:08:44.000
I was always their target!

135
00:08:53.050 --> 00:08:55.510
You're one persistent old fart.

136
00:08:55.510 --> 00:08:57.480
Garp's been weakened!

137
00:08:57.480 --> 00:09:00.940
That's our Shiryu! He's awesome!

138
00:09:00.940 --> 00:09:03.900
Even we might be able to finish him now!

139
00:09:04.860 --> 00:09:05.860
Let's go!

140
00:09:06.860 --> 00:09:07.990
Kill him!

141
00:09:07.990 --> 00:09:11.360
Charge! Our ticket to the good life
is right in front of us!

142
00:09:11.360 --> 00:09:12.820
Bring him down!

143
00:09:13.320 --> 00:09:16.830
Garp has a three-crown bounty,
same as an admiral!

144
00:09:16.830 --> 00:09:19.330
That's like three billion berries!

145
00:09:37.390 --> 00:09:38.310
Kuzan!

146
00:09:38.310 --> 00:09:40.060
Out of the way, amateurs!

147
00:09:46.320 --> 00:09:50.820
Even if you bound his hands and feet,
there's no way punks like you...

148
00:09:52.450 --> 00:09:53.950
could ever kill Garp!

149
00:09:58.200 --> 00:09:59.950
Ice Glove!

150
00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:10.130
Garp.

151
00:10:14.300 --> 00:10:15.970
Make me your student.

152
00:10:17.810 --> 00:10:19.640
My student?

153
00:10:20.640 --> 00:10:22.600
No thanks. I fly solo.

154
00:10:22.600 --> 00:10:24.560
Go learn from the Marine instructors.

155
00:10:24.560 --> 00:10:27.730
I've learned all I can from them.
I'm ready for the next level.

156
00:10:27.730 --> 00:10:29.650
Make me your student!

157
00:10:29.650 --> 00:10:31.530
Fat chance! Now scram!

158
00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:47.380
Ow!

159
00:10:47.380 --> 00:10:49.380
That hurts...

160
00:10:51.670 --> 00:10:53.590
Don't use haki!

161
00:10:54.470 --> 00:10:56.340
You won't get any stronger if you do.

162
00:10:56.340 --> 00:10:58.550
I don't know how to use it yet.

163
00:11:02.470 --> 00:11:04.390
I'm gonna do this!

164
00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:45.680
What exactly do the Marines consider justice?

165
00:11:45.680 --> 00:11:49.230
Ever since Ohara, I can't tell anymore.

166
00:11:54.360 --> 00:11:56.950
My son became a revolutionary!

167
00:11:56.950 --> 00:11:57.820
What?

168
00:12:01.950 --> 00:12:03.910
Damn it all!

169
00:12:12.130 --> 00:12:13.550
Kuzan!

170
00:12:13.880 --> 00:12:15.210
What's wrong?

171
00:12:15.210 --> 00:12:17.930
My grandson keeps going on
about becoming a pirate!

172
00:12:17.930 --> 00:12:18.550
Whoa...

173
00:12:18.550 --> 00:12:20.390
As if I'd ever let that happen!

174
00:12:20.390 --> 00:12:22.640
And that's my problem, how?

175
00:12:22.640 --> 00:12:25.470
Hey Kuzan, let's grab a bite.

176
00:12:25.470 --> 00:12:27.390
I'm a little busy.

177
00:12:27.390 --> 00:12:28.730
I'm an admiral, remember?

178
00:12:28.730 --> 00:12:29.900
How about tea?

179
00:12:29.900 --> 00:12:31.310
Seriously?!

180
00:12:37.570 --> 00:12:40.570
You trained one troublesome enemy.

181
00:12:41.030 --> 00:12:44.030
Consider yourself expelled, my foolish student.

182
00:13:17.280 --> 00:13:19.030
Vice Admiral Garp!

183
00:13:22.070 --> 00:13:23.700
Garp!

184
00:13:24.450 --> 00:13:26.370
Not bad, rookie...

185
00:13:29.080 --> 00:13:30.410
We have to defend Garp!

186
00:13:32.370 --> 00:13:36.340
I wouldn't count on getting away if I were you!

187
00:13:37.000 --> 00:13:39.380
This is Beehive!

188
00:13:39.380 --> 00:13:42.840
The more you poke it,
the more pirates swarm out!

189
00:13:42.840 --> 00:13:47.430
Do you really think
that ship off the coast is safe?

190
00:13:47.430 --> 00:13:48.390
What?

191
00:13:51.520 --> 00:13:55.310
You better not under-meow-stimate
the power of my Isle-Isle Fruit!

192
00:13:58.150 --> 00:13:59.280
Hibari!

193
00:13:59.280 --> 00:14:01.200
Thank goodness! You're awake!

194
00:14:01.950 --> 00:14:04.700
Where could Koby be?!

195
00:14:04.700 --> 00:14:07.830
I'm sorry... I caused you all so much trouble!

196
00:14:08.660 --> 00:14:10.700
He'll be here any minute.

197
00:14:10.700 --> 00:14:12.620
I'm just glad you're okay.

198
00:14:24.970 --> 00:14:26.760
H-Huh? What's that?

199
00:14:29.680 --> 00:14:33.690
All you see in the newspapers
is "Blackbeard this," "Blackbeard that"...

200
00:14:33.690 --> 00:14:36.900
Well maybe we want a little infamy, too!

201
00:14:37.150 --> 00:14:41.190
Let me give mew an exclusive look
at tomorrow morning's headline!

202
00:14:41.190 --> 00:14:47.030
"An elite unit of young Marines,
led by the famous Vice Admiral Garp...

203
00:14:47.830 --> 00:14:52.200
attempted to rescue Captain Koby,
the Hero of the Marines!

204
00:15:20.320 --> 00:15:26.820
But the captain of the Blackbeard
Pirates' fourth ship, Avalo Pizarro...

205
00:15:28.820 --> 00:15:32.740
utilized his terrifying power...

206
00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:36.710
and tragically annihilated them...

207
00:15:37.420 --> 00:15:40.420
at Pirate Island!"

208
00:15:45.920 --> 00:15:47.930
No! Please stop!

209
00:15:47.930 --> 00:15:49.390
Everyone is on that ship!

210
00:15:49.760 --> 00:15:51.890
Even civilians!

211
00:15:51.890 --> 00:15:53.430
Koby...

212
00:15:56.890 --> 00:15:58.810
Don't lose your cool.

213
00:16:02.480 --> 00:16:05.360
Justice will always prevail!

214
00:16:05.400 --> 00:16:09.200
<b>A Few Weeks Ago

Amazon Lily, the Isle of Women</b>

215
00:16:11.830 --> 00:16:13.330
Stop!

216
00:16:15.580 --> 00:16:20.460
We're gonna have... a whole lotta fun!

217
00:16:20.460 --> 00:16:22.090
Walk faster!

218
00:16:22.090 --> 00:16:23.170
Stop!

219
00:16:23.170 --> 00:16:24.300
Let us go!

220
00:16:24.300 --> 00:16:28.470
Who knows what they'll do
to us once we reach Pirate Island!

221
00:16:32.050 --> 00:16:35.600
I didn't expect Rayleigh's little interruption,

222
00:16:36.270 --> 00:16:39.230
but we still ended up
with some nice souvenirs!

223
00:16:42.150 --> 00:16:45.780
Vice Admiral, can't we do anything
about our comrades being taken away?

224
00:16:46.400 --> 00:16:48.070
Do we just abandon them?

225
00:16:48.070 --> 00:16:50.280
We don't have the authorization.

226
00:16:51.070 --> 00:16:52.450
We're up against an Emperor.

227
00:16:52.450 --> 00:16:53.410
But...!

228
00:17:07.130 --> 00:17:08.590
Captain Koby!

229
00:17:08.970 --> 00:17:11.840
Vice Admiral! He's a member of SWORD!

230
00:17:11.840 --> 00:17:12.930
SWORD...

231
00:17:13.430 --> 00:17:16.310
Well if it isn't Koby the Hero!

232
00:17:16.310 --> 00:17:17.680
What's the matter?

233
00:17:17.680 --> 00:17:19.890
You want your buddies back?

234
00:17:20.390 --> 00:17:24.310
Well, go ahead and try.
We don't mind an all-out war.

235
00:17:24.310 --> 00:17:29.280
Right now, you're trying to commandeer
a battleship along with 800 Marines.

236
00:17:30.070 --> 00:17:34.200
Would you permit me to go in their place?

237
00:17:44.380 --> 00:17:47.340
You've got one hell of an ego, kid!

238
00:17:47.840 --> 00:17:51.550
But I'd say you're worth every last bit of it!

239
00:17:56.510 --> 00:17:58.100
What's going on?!

240
00:17:59.060 --> 00:18:00.180
No way...

241
00:18:00.180 --> 00:18:05.690
<b>Present Day

Beehive, Pirate Island</b>

242
00:18:00.640 --> 00:18:04.060
What the hell is that thing?!

243
00:18:05.690 --> 00:18:07.150
<b>Present Day

Beehive, Pirate Island</b>

244
00:18:16.490 --> 00:18:17.910
Shoot it! Shoot it!

245
00:18:27.460 --> 00:18:30.170
Cannons don't work?!

246
00:18:30.670 --> 00:18:32.170
We need to get away!

247
00:18:32.170 --> 00:18:33.630
Full speed ahead!

248
00:18:34.930 --> 00:18:37.550
Like hell I'm letting you escape!

249
00:18:41.520 --> 00:18:43.480
What terrifying power...

250
00:18:43.480 --> 00:18:47.440
<b>On Pirate Island</b>

251
00:18:49.190 --> 00:18:55.610
If that massive hand slams down on them,
hundreds of soldiers and civilians will die!

252
00:18:55.950 --> 00:18:57.120
There's no way!

253
00:18:57.120 --> 00:18:58.620
We can't stop that thing!

254
00:18:59.370 --> 00:19:01.120
Prepare to abandon ship!

255
00:19:01.120 --> 00:19:04.330
Those inside, get on deck
and protect the civilians!

256
00:19:04.830 --> 00:19:06.540
This is all my fault!

257
00:19:06.540 --> 00:19:09.500
Everyone's going to die because of me!

258
00:19:13.420 --> 00:19:16.340
Did I make the wrong decision?!

259
00:19:17.300 --> 00:19:19.510
I couldn't even save a single person!

260
00:19:20.180 --> 00:19:22.430
I can't save anyone!

261
00:19:35.450 --> 00:19:38.870
What should I do?!

262
00:19:38.870 --> 00:19:40.080
You guys...

263
00:19:45.370 --> 00:19:46.500
can save them!

264
00:19:49.420 --> 00:19:51.380
Vice Admiral Garp!

265
00:19:55.010 --> 00:19:56.510
Alright, men...

266
00:19:57.340 --> 00:19:59.050
Listen up.

267
00:20:00.510 --> 00:20:03.220
I'm going to give you an opening!

268
00:20:04.220 --> 00:20:06.810
First up, Captain Koby!

269
00:20:06.810 --> 00:20:10.690
You'll pulverize that island monster's hand!

270
00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:12.400
What?!

271
00:20:12.400 --> 00:20:14.110
How do you expect me to do that?

272
00:20:14.110 --> 00:20:19.200
Rear Admiral Grus, you'll protect
the ship from the hand's debris!

273
00:20:19.200 --> 00:20:20.030
Huh?!

274
00:20:20.030 --> 00:20:23.990
Lieutenant Commander Helmeppo,
don't let anyone stand in the way of those two!

275
00:20:23.990 --> 00:20:25.580
Anyone?!

276
00:20:25.580 --> 00:20:27.460
Vice Admiral Garp!

277
00:20:27.460 --> 00:20:29.000
But that's...

278
00:20:29.500 --> 00:20:31.290
There's no room for hesitation!

279
00:20:32.210 --> 00:20:35.170
Hop to it!

280
00:20:44.310 --> 00:20:45.060
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

281
00:20:52.400 --> 00:20:54.360
Koby and the others are on the move!

282
00:20:56.320 --> 00:20:57.490
It's pointless!

283
00:20:57.490 --> 00:20:59.650
What are you supposed to do without Garp?!

284
00:20:59.650 --> 00:21:01.740
We'll send you all to the bottom of the sea!

285
00:21:03.700 --> 00:21:04.870
Here they come!

286
00:21:04.870 --> 00:21:06.700
Helmeppo! Take care of them!

287
00:21:06.700 --> 00:21:08.790
What?! Me?!

288
00:21:08.790 --> 00:21:10.710
You heard Vice Admiral Garp!

289
00:21:10.710 --> 00:21:12.710
Dammit! Why is it always me?!

290
00:21:13.880 --> 00:21:16.170
Bring it on!

291
00:21:17.420 --> 00:21:18.670
That's too many!

292
00:21:18.670 --> 00:21:20.800
Way too many! Hey, one at a time!

293
00:21:20.800 --> 00:21:21.890
Hey, Koby!

294
00:21:21.890 --> 00:21:23.300
He told you to destroy it.

295
00:21:23.300 --> 00:21:24.890
You got some kind of bomb?

296
00:21:24.890 --> 00:21:26.470
Afraid not!

297
00:21:26.470 --> 00:21:28.640
But I have to figure something out!

298
00:21:28.640 --> 00:21:29.850
Figure something out?!

299
00:21:30.190 --> 00:21:33.060
It's big enough to grab and crush a battleship!

300
00:21:33.980 --> 00:21:35.320
I know!

301
00:21:35.320 --> 00:21:38.190
I won't let you get away, Koby!

302
00:21:39.240 --> 00:21:40.450
Oh, crap!

303
00:21:43.660 --> 00:21:44.780
Koby!

304
00:21:45.660 --> 00:21:48.910
Don't let anyone stand
in the way of those two!

305
00:21:49.290 --> 00:21:51.330
Oh, give me a break!

306
00:21:53.380 --> 00:21:54.630
I'm leaving the rest...

307
00:21:55.920 --> 00:21:57.000
to you!

308
00:21:57.750 --> 00:21:59.260
Get lost!

309
00:22:01.170 --> 00:22:02.880
Helmeppo!

310
00:22:02.880 --> 00:22:05.140
Eyes on the prize, Koby!

311
00:22:05.140 --> 00:22:06.050
But...

312
00:22:06.050 --> 00:22:06.850
Keep moving!

313
00:22:13.730 --> 00:22:16.820
Garp, where do you think you're going?

314
00:22:19.650 --> 00:22:21.610
You're in no shape to fight.

315
00:22:22.860 --> 00:22:24.870
It's just a scratch.

316
00:22:29.540 --> 00:22:32.080
I'm just looking out for you.

317
00:22:32.580 --> 00:22:34.420
You're too soft!

318
00:23:06.780 --> 00:23:08.030
Garp!

319
00:23:08.030 --> 00:23:09.530
Why is he coming this way?!

320
00:23:09.950 --> 00:23:12.950
Wait! Don't you care
what happens to the ship?!

321
00:23:13.580 --> 00:23:16.040
Galaxy...

322
00:23:16.040 --> 00:23:19.000
Divide!

323
00:23:43.780 --> 00:23:45.780
The arm is recoiling!

324
00:23:48.740 --> 00:23:50.620
Is this what he meant by an opening?!

325
00:23:50.620 --> 00:23:52.240
The arm pulled back!

326
00:23:52.240 --> 00:23:53.750
What are you gonna do, Koby?!

327
00:23:58.420 --> 00:23:59.880
I'll make him proud!

328
00:24:02.300 --> 00:24:03.250
Koby!

329
00:24:07.590 --> 00:24:11.050
You geriatric bastard!

330
00:24:14.060 --> 00:24:17.640
Something like that isn't
enough to stop me, Garp!

331
00:24:17.640 --> 00:24:20.520
Now mew've really pissed me off!

332
00:24:20.520 --> 00:24:24.900
Enjoy the front row seat...

333
00:24:24.900 --> 00:24:28.070
to the death of your comrades!

334
00:24:28.070 --> 00:24:31.070
They're about to be hisstory!

335
00:24:31.070 --> 00:24:33.030
It's coming back around!

336
00:24:33.030 --> 00:24:38.000
There's no way mew can save them all in time!

337
00:24:39.170 --> 00:24:40.960
Hey, Helmeppo.

338
00:24:40.960 --> 00:24:45.510
Koby's made some real progress,
but it seems like he's always beat up.

339
00:24:45.510 --> 00:24:47.380
He's always beat up?

340
00:24:47.380 --> 00:24:48.680
Oh...

341
00:24:48.680 --> 00:24:51.300
He told me not to tell you, but...

342
00:25:00.230 --> 00:25:05.360
I'm not a natural fighter like the others,
so ten times the effort isn't enough!

343
00:25:05.360 --> 00:25:10.110
If I want to be the kind
of Marine who can protect people,

344
00:25:10.110 --> 00:25:14.280
I have to train 100 times—
no, 200 times harder!

345
00:25:22.130 --> 00:25:23.750
You damn idiot!

346
00:25:23.750 --> 00:25:25.250
Enough is enough!

347
00:25:25.250 --> 00:25:27.340
Please, you have to stop!

348
00:25:27.800 --> 00:25:29.720
You've gotta be kidding...

349
00:25:29.720 --> 00:25:32.300
He's been doing extra training
in addition to mine?

350
00:25:32.300 --> 00:25:35.720
Yes sir, he never skips a night.

351
00:25:35.970 --> 00:25:37.430
He punches the battleship bags...

352
00:25:44.480 --> 00:25:46.360
until his fists...

353
00:25:46.860 --> 00:25:48.690
are bruised and bloody.

354
00:25:57.910 --> 00:26:01.160
Gotta make it!

355
00:26:01.790 --> 00:26:05.290
Gotta make it!

356
00:26:09.960 --> 00:26:11.300
Is that...

357
00:26:14.550 --> 00:26:16.050
Koby!

358
00:26:16.600 --> 00:26:20.480
Captain Koby!

359
00:26:20.480 --> 00:26:22.730
Look! It's Koby!

360
00:26:22.730 --> 00:26:24.730
Is he trying to stop the hand?!

361
00:26:24.730 --> 00:26:26.190
It's impossible!

362
00:26:26.190 --> 00:26:28.610
Compared to that hand, he's like an ant!

363
00:26:28.610 --> 00:26:32.150
He must've let all that hero talk go to his head!

364
00:26:32.150 --> 00:26:36.530
Koby! It's dangerous up there!

365
00:26:36.530 --> 00:26:38.120
Get away, Koby!

366
00:26:40.120 --> 00:26:46.460
Watch as your ship gets smashed
and your men die screaming!

367
00:26:46.460 --> 00:26:50.800
Even if they dive into the sea,
Aokiji will just freeze them!

368
00:26:52.760 --> 00:26:55.720
Serves you right!

369
00:27:00.270 --> 00:27:02.770
These people's lives are in my hands!

370
00:27:08.060 --> 00:27:09.440
I have to destroy it!

371
00:27:10.190 --> 00:27:12.400
If I can't, they'll all die!

372
00:27:13.740 --> 00:27:16.490
I'm not a natural fighter like the others,

373
00:27:17.370 --> 00:27:19.080
so ten times the effort isn't enough!

374
00:27:24.580 --> 00:27:26.370
I have to train 100 times—

375
00:27:27.330 --> 00:27:28.880
no, 200 times harder!

376
00:27:31.750 --> 00:27:35.010
What did you guys join the Marines to save?

377
00:27:36.970 --> 00:27:38.390
Koby!

378
00:27:38.390 --> 00:27:40.760
We're out of time! Abandon ship!

379
00:27:44.140 --> 00:27:46.690
You guys can save them!

380
00:27:55.150 --> 00:27:58.410
Honesty...

381
00:27:58.410 --> 00:28:01.910
Impact!

382
00:28:38.910 --> 00:28:41.030
When the hell did he learn to do that?!

383
00:28:41.030 --> 00:28:42.530
Incredible!

384
00:28:42.530 --> 00:28:45.040
But what should we do about the debris?

385
00:28:49.210 --> 00:28:52.670
I won't let a speck of rubble hit that ship!

386
00:29:01.340 --> 00:29:02.890
Glorp Web!

387
00:29:05.390 --> 00:29:07.930
Koby!

388
00:29:10.850 --> 00:29:12.520
Koby!

389
00:29:12.520 --> 00:29:14.940
I can't believe you did it!

390
00:29:16.900 --> 00:29:18.360
Helmeppo...

391
00:29:18.820 --> 00:29:20.740
I really did...

392
00:29:23.450 --> 00:29:26.120
You're crazy, y'know that?!

393
00:29:26.120 --> 00:29:27.620
Freakin' crazy!

394
00:29:28.710 --> 00:29:32.960
You obliterated an arm the size of a mountain!

395
00:29:37.760 --> 00:29:40.550
Let's head home, you doofus!

396
00:29:47.430 --> 00:29:48.890
Captain Koby!

397
00:29:48.890 --> 00:29:50.390
Helmeppo!

398
00:29:50.390 --> 00:29:52.480
I'm so glad that you're alive!

399
00:29:52.850 --> 00:29:54.730
Koby!

400
00:29:57.110 --> 00:29:58.610
Hibari...

401
00:29:59.190 --> 00:30:00.860
What a relief.

402
00:30:00.860 --> 00:30:03.610
I'm so glad you're okay.

403
00:30:05.580 --> 00:30:08.830
Now we just need to wait for
Vice Admiral Garp and we can depart.

404
00:30:14.880 --> 00:30:16.710
This is Garp.

405
00:30:16.710 --> 00:30:19.760
Operation "Retrieve Captain Koby" is complete.

406
00:30:20.130 --> 00:30:21.760
Vice Admiral Garp!

407
00:30:21.760 --> 00:30:23.010
Thank goodness!

408
00:30:23.010 --> 00:30:24.970
Hurry up and come back to the ship!

409
00:30:25.470 --> 00:30:26.970
Now then...

410
00:30:27.930 --> 00:30:31.390
Get away from Beehive. Full speed ahead.

411
00:30:31.980 --> 00:30:33.060
What?

412
00:30:33.810 --> 00:30:36.020
What are you talking about, Garp?!

413
00:30:36.020 --> 00:30:38.730
I'll be just fine, so don't worry.

414
00:30:39.070 --> 00:30:43.530
Your collective safety is our top priority.

415
00:30:44.160 --> 00:30:45.490
Isn't that right?

416
00:30:50.160 --> 00:30:51.500
No, but...

417
00:30:51.500 --> 00:30:53.250
Prince, turn the ship aroun–

418
00:30:54.960 --> 00:30:56.920
This incident will no doubt...

419
00:30:58.500 --> 00:31:01.380
serve as a warning to pirates everywhere!

420
00:31:04.470 --> 00:31:07.100
Please let me join the Marines!

421
00:31:07.100 --> 00:31:12.100
I'll gladly be a cabin boy or whatever else
if it means I can be a Marine!

422
00:31:13.730 --> 00:31:17.480
What did you guys join the Marines to save?

423
00:31:18.940 --> 00:31:21.280
It was the futures of the people, right?

424
00:31:21.820 --> 00:31:26.490
In that case, you kids have got a lot
more life left in you than some damn geezer!

425
00:31:28.030 --> 00:31:29.990
So take that baby...

426
00:31:31.290 --> 00:31:33.040
and live on!

427
00:31:51.180 --> 00:31:52.930
Keep moving forward!

428
00:31:54.310 --> 00:31:56.190
You guys are all the future...

429
00:31:56.810 --> 00:31:58.480
of the Marines!

430
00:32:09.240 --> 00:32:11.030
Vice Admiral Garp!

431
00:32:11.030 --> 00:32:13.910
Never give another lecture like that!

432
00:32:13.910 --> 00:32:15.330
All lives are equal!

433
00:32:16.410 --> 00:32:19.000
But youngsters have infinite potential!

434
00:32:32.390 --> 00:32:38.350
The following day, newspapers would report on
the rescue of the young Captain Koby, Hero of the Marines,

435
00:32:39.020 --> 00:32:45.320
the disappearance of Vice Admiral Garp,
the Legendary Hero, on Pirate Island,

436
00:32:45.780 --> 00:32:54.700
and Emperor Straw Hat Luffy barricading
himself on Future Island, Egghead.

437
00:32:54.700 --> 00:33:00.000
"Straw Hat..."

438
00:33:06.450 --> 00:33:11.540
Running so long lost track of just how long its been

439
00:33:12.390 --> 00:33:18.900
Collected scars while striving not even trying beneath my skin

440
00:33:19.400 --> 00:33:26.320
But in the back of my head the dream is not dead I remember a map

441
00:33:26.400 --> 00:33:32.610
to a treasure still gleaming its within our grasp

442
00:33:32.750 --> 00:33:39.520
Can you feel my heart Feelings I impart

443
00:33:39.480 --> 00:33:46.630
The promises are there theyre deep down but still primed to share

444
00:33:46.760 --> 00:33:55.740
Peerless dreams kept close the dreams that always matter most

445
00:33:55.920 --> 00:34:01.490
Before we set sail why not raise a toast

446
00:34:01.610 --> 00:34:08.520
So I pen this note to you Dear sunrise Ill see you soon

447
00:34:08.680 --> 00:34:15.710
See the smile I saw the day that I sang this song to you

448
00:34:15.690 --> 00:34:22.760
And regardless of our age these memries will still remain

449
00:34:22.660 --> 00:34:29.870
Wont forget until this wish makes it to you
